p: Territory of Washington 3rd Judicial District S.S. In District Court holding terms at Seattle in King County. In the matter of the application of Author Hain for a writ of Habeas Corpus On this 5th day of October A. D. 1878 comes the Sheriff of said King County, L. V. Wyckoff and produces the body of said Author Hain and makes return of the writ of Habeas Corpus heretofore issued herein. And now the previously his counsel J. M. Hall, Esq. excepts to the suffiicience of said return and moves for the discharge of the prisioner from custody pending the consideration whereof the further leaving of this matter is adjourned until Monday the 9th day of October 1878 at 10 o clock in the morning. And now on this 9th day of October 1878 at the appointed hour causes the said Sheriff and holding the body of the said author Hain as heretofore and the further consideration of this matter is resumed And now after adjournment and being fully advised in the premises it is now hold considered and adjourned thats so
